meanings.definition: The act of processing something excessively.
meanings.sent1: The overprocessing of paperwork led to delays in the project.
meanings.sent2: Overprocessing can sometimes result in wasted time and resources.
meanings.sent3: The comedy skit humorously portrayed the chaos caused by overprocessing.
meanings.sent4: The overprocessing of images in the film gave it a surreal quality.
meanings.sent5: The overprocessing of emotions can sometimes lead to misunderstandings in relationships.
